          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-06-24T13:33:17Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Students Not Profits Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill makes certain institutions of higher education (IHEs) ineligible to receive federal financial student assistance.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill makes for-profit institutions of higher education ineligible to receive such assistance. The bill also makes ineligible any institution that has (1) filed for bankruptcy; (2) been convicted of, or pled nolo contendere or guilty to, a crime involving federal student aid; (3) committed fraud, substantial misrepresentation, or false certification involving federal student aid; or (4) executive officers who were previously employed at an institution receiving federal student aid that closed.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill establishes certain criteria that an IHE must meet to be eligible for conversion from a for-profit IHE to a nonprofit IHE. Before approving such conversion, the Department of Education must publish the application in the Federal Register for notice and comment.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-10-17T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
